node.text:
Spoken word poet & Hollister model, @khyriesha, is on the mic to honor Juneteenth in her own words:
"This day to me, is more than a day. To me it’s a celebration of the lives we are now able to have after the many years of being enslaved. This day is our Independence Day, representing the freedom we now have & what we can do with our freedom that we weren’t able to do before."

node.text: Hey! It’s Daniela Marquez, @danielabelindaa, and I’m a Hollister Brand Agent. I have always been proud of who I am whether it was based on my cultural roots or traditions. At a young age, I was taught to speak up and show courage to the world! I am coming here today to participate in Volume ON because I have a voice that needs to be heard around the world. It’s important to encourage every individual to take a stand because everyone’s feelings are valid. I’m here to show my love and inspiration in owning one’s voice! Thank you.

node.text:
Hiiii! My name is Christian Martinez, @christianm.03. I’m a first generation Mexican American. I’m also gay. My platform is used to spread positivity. I live in a small community in New Jersey. I’m a big activist within my community and I’m striving to make the world a better place. 

I participated in Volume ON because I want to let you guys know that you aren’t alone in this fight for human rights! I want to shed light to what me and other Black and brown people have to endure in our everyday lives. It’s important for you guys to know my story so you can empathize for the challenges we have to face in our daily lives and so you understand why we are so actively motivated in this social justice movement. I want you to understand my pain and my reasons for my motives. 

If we can understand each other on a deeper level, we can be more united. I’m 1 of millions of Latino kids that are fighting for their lives. I hope one day we can live in a world where we can all be confident with our identities.

node.text:
Storytelling is such a powerful way to share wisdom and spread change. I was so excited to join the Volume ON campaign and hear the stories of other BIPOC and share my own.
 
We owe it to everyone to start investing in ourselves and our communities! I urge you to continue having conversations and listening to the voices and experiences of Black folks. There are so many resources out there to support you when it comes to educating yourself on these issues! The time is now to truly start reimagining about how our world could look like, especially when we are caring for each other's needs and build authentic and transformative relationships.
